Zodidi Mhlana JOHANNESBURG- A security guard sustained minor injuries after a cash-in-transit heist on the Marikana Road near Kroondal. ER24 Spokesperson, Russel Meiring said that the guard sustained a gunshot wound to his lower leg. “When paramedics, along with various other services, arrived on the scene to find a cash-in-transit van in the middle of the road. The vehicle had been completely ripped open with debris lying across the entire scene. A light motor vehicle was also parked a short distance away, riddled with bullet holes. One man was found to have sustained a gunshot wound to his lower leg. Paramedics treated the man and thereafter transported him to a nearby private hospital for further treatment,” Meiring said. He said that the details concerning the cash-in-transit heist are still being investigated. @Mhlana
